processDescription: I wanted to head towards the outer areas to try to find the hotspots.
I stayed on nodes that had a higher payout until they began to display diminishing returns.

In the first round my strategy was to identify a high value node by clicking at random the first couple of trials and after that by using the connections as a guide.\nIn the second round my strategy was to uncover as many nodes as possible to be able to provide an accurate guess and pick a high value node when asked to.\n
I looked for patterns and noticed the outer nodes tended to have more points

I wanted to seek out higher paying nodes, then search beside them to see if they lead to a higher paying one, and go with the highest paying one I could find in a few clicks. At a certain point I\'d just stop searching and click the highest one revealed to me.

As stated, the more connections it had the bigger potential it had. So, my strategy was to try and select more clustered positions and occasionally branch out. Since the number of clicks were limited, I settled for 60+% of the max value where available.
I reclicked nodes that had a high point value.

I would begin by clicking a few towards the end of the line. They often had a lot of points, then I would click backwards if those points were high and continue to click them if they were over the point value of 70.

I picked end nodes that only had one connection many times because it seemed like that was where the highest value was. I tried to remember how the patterns on the examples looked when choosing end nodes to click.
I tried to find a higher one and click around it until I found one 90+ which I would continually click

I had the vague sense that the higher-point nodes were at the fringe of the network, and that if you determine where the start node was, you might observe that the lower-point nodes were close to the beginning and increased in value at the tail end. Also, where the nodes were denser, the values seemed to have less spread, but I didn\'t really look too closely.
I tried to use what I knew about the examples to find the patterns in the real game.
tried to pick one\'s at the end of a series

I typically stayed to the outside edges & tended to find the largest numbers there. The smaller numbers tended to be on the inside, so I stayed away from those.
I tried to find the nodes that were >80 points.

If a node has a high value, the other nodes connect to it would have a high value too so I would click 2 to 3 of them and re-click the one with the highest value. If the shown node has a low value, I would click the nodes that are on the edge of the network until I find one with a high value.
i noticed higher numbers are bunched up together so i always tend to go in that area

I tried to find the higher numbered nodes and then I followed them to see which ones would lead to more nodes that have a higher score.

Clicking on the ending nodes, that lose connection, seemed to give the highest results. I didn\'t really figure out until the final one that I could click on a high number over and over again to get more points: whoops. I thought you meant you could hit a back button to the previous page to do a node again. I didn\'t realize you meant a number on the same node. What I mean is, I thought the larger area consisting of little circles WAS the node. I hope that made sense.
find the highest and stay with it

I noticed that largest numbers tended to be clustered near \"ends\" of the connected links, so I went for those. Once I had found one that seemed pretty large (80\'s, 90\'s) I figured it was better to get as many points as I could on that one, than risk opening up ones that could be worth very few points.

I tried sampling nodes that connected many other nodes, then if it was high, I would branch out to try and hone in on the highest nodes. If I found something reasonably high like 70+ then I committed to it for the remainder of the clicks.

I felt like the outer nodes would give more points, and for the most part I was correct. I did a few clicks at the beginning of each round on outer nodes until I found a node with a high point value. After I found a point value I was happy with I clicked that node until the round was over. I thought I did pretty well on this hit and that my strategy worked great!
